@node 2 "  Installation"
@font XCourier.font 13
  
  System requirements for installation: OS 2.04 ++, C/IconX.
  System requirements for use: OS 2.04 ++, harddisk.
  Tested on A1200, OS 3.0
  -----------------------
  Please read this documentation very carefully, especially all
  warnings. All use is at your own risk.


  Install all files   o n l y   in this order:
     
  1. Use <install_english> first to install all files the program
     needs to work, especially hbasic2.library.
  
  2. Now use <pw input> to set in your personal password and your
     name and address. You can choose another order as it is usual
     in your country, when inputting your name and address.
     
  From now on the boot process will be interrupted until <pw> reads
  the correct password input. Enter your password exactly in the same
  way you saved it with <pw input> (with capital or no capital letters,
  too).  

  If there is accidently no password setting with <pw input>, next reset
  will show you a window with an according notice. Then enter <pw> (with
  no brackets) as password to start your computer.
@endnode
@node 3 "  Change password"
@font XCourier.font 13

  
  To change your password use <pw input> again.
  It overwrites all old settings.
@endnode
@node 4 "  Delete password"
@font XCourier.font 13


  To delete <pw> und <pw.dat> from your harddisk use <delete pw>.
@endnode
@node 5 "  Warnings"
@font XCourier.font 13

  Attention!
  
  Make sure to have a bootable and intact Workbench floppy disk.
  It is the only way to start your computer when <pw> misinterprets
  unclear inputs.
    
  If this happened, put this disk into your floppy drive and boot your
  Amiga. Then open your WB-directory "S" on your harddisk and delete the
  files <pw> and  <pw.dat>.
  Then your can boot your Amiga from harddisk again. 
@endnode
